[{"id":"VR610776","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a river that moves from left to right with a current of speed v sub r. A point is indicated at the mid point of the bottom side of the river bank. Two arrows extend from the point. The first arrow is labeled Boat 1 and extends vertically upward toward the top of the page. The second arrow is labeled Boat 2 and extends upward and to the right. A coordinate plane indicates that the y value is upward toward the top of the page and the x value is rightward.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR610776.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two boats cross a river that has a current of velocity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub r\"><math alttext=\"v sub r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></math></span></span>, as shown. The boats have identical speeds with respect to the water. Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> heads at an angle upstream such that it reaches the opposite shore directly across from its starting point. Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> heads in a direction perpendicular to the current and reaches a position on the opposite shore downstream of its starting point. Which boat takes less time to cross the river, and what reasoning supports this claim?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR610776_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> takes less time because it travels a shorter distance than Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> takes less time because its velocity with respect to the water and the current velocity add together, giving Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> a greater resultant velocity.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> takes less time because its velocity has a greater <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-component with respect to the ground than Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Boat <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> takes less time because the current increases the boatâ€™s speed relative to the ground.</p>"],"answer":2}]